Lagos state has recorded four more COVID19 deaths. This was disclosed via the state’s Ministry of Health’s Twitter handle this afternoon. This brings to 42 the number of COVID19 related deaths recorded in the state. ”199 new cases of #COVID19 Infection confirmed. Total confirmed cases in Lagos as at 20th of May is 2,970. 17 #COVID19Lagos patients; 6 females & 11 males were discharged. Total Discharged now 649. 4 COVID19 deaths were recorded. This brings the number of #COVID19 related death in Lagos to 42.” the tweet read. See the tweet below: The Lagos State Government on Wednesday announced the death of another COVID-19 related patient, barely 24 hours after the sixth death was recorded. It also announced that 25 new cases were recorded, bringing the total confirmed cases in the state to 217. The State Ministry of Health made this known… April 15, 2020 In "News" The Kano State government has confirmed the death of two more patients who tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in the state. The state Ministry of Health announced this in a tweet, saying that was the situation in Kano as of 12:15pm on Monday. This brings the total number of COVID-19… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - For the first time the COVID-19 pandemic has found its way in Imo State. This brings the total number of states so far affected to 28 in addition to the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja. According to the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) in its latest update… April 26, 2020 In "Top Stories"